---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="About — Your Name" description="UX Design Consultant at Deloitte working at the intersection of research, service design, and systems thinking.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 md:px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <header class="mb-16">
      <p class="text-xs font-mono text-amber-400 tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">About</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-stone-100 leading-tight max-w-2xl">
        Your Name
      </h1>
      <p class="text-stone-400 font-mono text-sm mt-3">UX Design Consultant · Deloitte · Montréal</p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 mb-24">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 text-stone-400 leading-relaxed">
        <p>Good design isn't enough anymore. Everything looks decent — that's table stakes.</p>
        <p>What I care about is whether the work is deliberate. Connected to a real need, shaped by real constraints, and part of a broader narrative that actually moves something forward.</p>
        <p>I've spent most of my career in complex, high-stakes systems — government services, financial platforms, enterprise products where the cost of getting it wrong is real. That context has made me allergic to work that exists for its own sake. Form follows function isn't just a principle, it's a filter: if you can't explain why something is there, it probably shouldn't be.</p>
        <p>The best results happen when design and product are thinking together from the start — not when design is cleaning up after decisions that were already made.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-12">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Capabilities</h2>
          <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2" role="list">
            {[
              "Generative & evaluative research",
              "Service design & journey mapping",
              "Information architecture",
              "Stakeholder alignment & facilitation",
              "Systems thinking",
              "Accessibility & inclusive design",
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="text-sm text-stone-400 flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true">—</span>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Currently</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-400">UX Design Consultant at Deloitte, working on enterprise and public sector digital transformation.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Contact</h2>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
            <a href="mailto:your@email.com" class="text-sm font-mono text-stone-400 hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors">your@email.com</a>
            <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/yourhandle" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-sm font-mono text-stone-400 hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors">LinkedIn</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-stone-800 pt-12">
      <a href="/work" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-mono text-stone-500 hover:text-stone-100 transition-colors">
        <span aria-hidden="true">←</span>
        View my work
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>